RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG GINGER was nested behind the contesting leaders on the rail at the half, found a seam in the three path to bid for the lead in upper stretch, lane closed shortly thereafter at the eighth pole, bullied her through in deep stretch and got up edging away for the win nearing the wire. TIPSY MOON had a good spot outside watching the engaging pair at the half, loomed five wide at the three sixteenths pole, had a slim lead with a furlong to go but could not hold off the rushing winner in deep stretch. STOLE THE RING was bumped outside at the break, stalked on the rail near the back of the pack at the half, could see the field just off the fence straightening out for the drive, shifted out behind horses five wide at the furlong marker and closed with a rush to capture third money. HUMOR ME JIM broke out at the start, pressed outside down the back straight, hounded the pacesetter throughout the turn in the two path, assumed control in the four path turning for home, drifted inwards in mid stretch and faded in the last sixteenth. THATSITTHATSALL settled in mid pack down the backside, was asked on the turn for more making little headway and could not get involved between runners down the stretch. SUMMER SNOW took command soon after the start on the rail, continued to narrowly dictate terms on the turn, was collared outside in upper stretch and retreated in the final sixteenth. DIXIE MORNING broke in to begin trailing down the backstretch, offered a mild run midpoint on the turn to contend at the top of the lane three wide and tired outside in mid stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ONE MORE BREW sat outside three deep in the tracking trio with three furlongs from the finish, made steady gain on the frontrunner throughout the turn, was in the thick of things four wide straightening out for the stretch drive, stubbornly dug in between foes at the eighth pole to surge late for the gritty win. JAMIESTA stalked near the rear down the back straight, put in a good sustained run three wide around horses commencing at the three furlong marker, bid six wide outside turning for home and stalled in the final sixteenth. ADELAIDE COURT broke out on the break, took this field running up front unchallenged down the backside, continued loose on the lead through the turn, was beginning to shorten stride in upper stretch, was asking for the wire at the furlong marker holding onto a diminishing lead and faded late to keep third money in the end. MOONQUEST broke in, was steadied soon after the start, trailed down the backside, could not catch up to the field running on the turn and was not a factor in the stretch drive. PRINCE SUSSEX broke sharp to begin, chased the lone speed early on, could not keep pace between foes with three eighths remaining and made no impact on the fence through to the finish line.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PONTIAC was just a bit reluctant to load, got away well racing mid-pack up the backstretch, shifted in to about the three path heading to the turn, moved out a path late on that bend beginning to pick it up, came out wider for the top of the stretch bumping with a rival, bumped repeatedly with that one through the stretch while dueling late and maintaining a short advantage from the sixteenth pole to the wire. BUCK'S FIZZ was given encouragement at the start but lacking speed, raced between foes off the pace into the turn, moved out from three to five wide on that bend advancing to be outside the eventual winner by the top of the stretch, was bumped by that one in upper stretch, came in just a bit and had several bumps thereafter while dueling late, was just held off. SIESTA BEACH broke outwardly bumping a rival, recovered well to track the leaders from inside, was in behind at the quarter pole, came out and found room three deep at the three-sixteenths, took the lead by the furlong marker while drifting out, continued to drift out under left-handed urging, was challenged and overtaken just past the sixteenth pole but fought on while best of the rest. SUMMER COMMANDER was energetic behind the gate and just a bit hard to load, broke on top and set the pace, faced pressure from an outside foe while racing just off the rail into and one the turn, put away that rival past the quarter pole but was challenged by another in upper stretch, yielded late. BRAVE DANCER broke outwardly, raced outside rivals toward the rear going four wide on the turn, kept on in the late stages but just missed the minor award. ALWAYS A WAY was shut off a few strides out of the gate, unhurriedly brought up the rear a long ways back of the leaders, came out for the stretch run, ran on well but far too late. FOREST WOODSMAN was bumped at the start, coaxed forward, raced outside a foe in the second group, went two to three wide on the turn coming to the quarter pole four deep and within striking range, lacked the needed late kick and drifted in a bit through the stretch. RED SNEAKERS broke a step slowly, raced toward the back inside rivals but off the fence, came out further in the stretch, ran on evenly. CANTUCCI was forced in at the start, raced last but one lacking speed, failed to menace. VALLEY VICTORY broke inwardly, moved forward to press the pace from outside going three wide on the turn, came up empty. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF BUCK'S FIZZ AGAINST PONTIAC, NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: READY FOR THE LADY travelled near the back of the pack just outside in the second flight in the beginning stages of the race, rated comfortably three deep outside challengers with four furlongs remaining, keeping a close eye on the engaging leaders, pushed the button to go three wide midpoint on the turn, bid four wide between horses at the top of the stretch and drew off out kicking runners in the last eighth. SIR SAHIB was unhurried trailing the field into the first turn, continued in last at the half but was only a few lengths off in the compact field, waited to pounce entering the final turn, followed the path of the winner with five sixteenths to go, angled out for clear running in the five path driving to the wire, was outfinished by the winner in mid stretch but closed strongly to garner second money in the end. ELUSIVE KNIGHT stalked on the rail near the rear in the second flight into the first turn, watched the front runner tracking inside down the backstretch, was urged to keep up when the running started three furlongs from home, could not find more on the fence turning for home and was not involved in the late stages of the race.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAR SIGN travelled in mid pack just off the fence, began to close in on the leaders while well in hand with three eighths to run, shifted five wide for the stretch run gaining momentum and found his best stride late to just get up in time right at the finish to win the bob on the line. PRICELESS WILL broke out to begin, was content tracking the lone speed on the turn, started to reel in the pacesetter at the quarter marker, poked his nose in front between foes at the sixteenth pole and lost in a tight photo at the wire. MAAKWA was off slow on the break, was coaxed for position to take command on the rail at the half, opened up on the field through the turn, was clinging to a narrow lead turning for home, stubbornly battled on the rail to the wire but was on the losing end of a three horse photo for the win at the finish showing a gritty effort in deep stretch. LENNY K was in tight at the start, co-trailed down the backstretch, began picking up runners advancing inside with three eighths to go, slipped up the fence to be in range at the top of the lane and put in a good run gaining late at the wire. KING ALFREDO settled in mid pack three deep down the back straight, made little presence three wide running on the turn and angled out widest in lane seven for the stretch drive and was one paced to the finish. RACE.FOOTNOTES: SARAH'S DANCER exchanged some light contact at the start, settled between runners mid-pack, switched out six wide leaving the turn, drove past inside the final sixteenth. BIJOU BABY stalked from outside, advanced on the leader three then four wide on the turn taking the lead at the top of the stretch, was headed in upper stretch, dueled with that inside foe, bested that one late but couldn't hold off the winner. ELLA FRANCES settled off the pace, advanced inside leaving the turn saving ground, bid inside taking a narrow lead in upper stretch, was outfinished but held show. MRS. C exchanged a light bump at the start, settled off the pace outside, began a rapid advance outside on the turn coming to the top of the stretch six to seven wide, gained steadily through the stretch but needed more and just missed show honors. WHERE'S SAMNBAILEY settled outside mid-pack, advanced four then five wide on the turn looming a threat in upper stretch but evened out. TAPPING A RHYTHM tracked inside a rival but well off the leader early, advanced on that on in behind racing just off the fence, steadied on heels slightly when in tight near the quarter pole, came out further past that juncture, ran on. WORRY LESS shifted in saving ground on the turn, ran on evenly. KNOTTY AND NICE lacked early speed, ran up on heels coming past the three-quarters and briefly was put to a hold, continued racing toward the back and was never near enough to threaten. MOONBRIGHT hesitated at the start spotting the field about five lengths, advanced outside foes into the turn, swung seven wide into the stretch, failed to threaten. ROSES ARE FREE broke sharply and quickly sped clear shifting in, set the pace racing about in the two path, gave way when headed late on the turn. FOLLOWING AN OBJECTION BY THE RIDER OF TAPPING A RHYTHM AGAINST BIJOU BABY ALLEGING INTERFERENCE NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.
